The Chinese species of the genus Ontsira Cameron (Hymenoptera, Braconidae, Doryctinae)Abstract The Chinese species of the genus Ontsira Cameron, 1900 (Hymenoptera: Braconidae, Doryctinae) are reviewed. Eleven species are recognized, of which four new species are described from China and South Korea: O. abbreviata sp. n., O. henana sp. n., O. robusta sp. n., and O. rugivertex sp. n. Two species, O. ignea (Ratzeburg) and O. neantica Belokobylskij et Maet√¥, are recorded in China for the first time. A key to the Asian species of the genus Ontsira is provided.